    "id": "f_csv_c2bccf960f",
    "slug": "some-survivors-can-be-wary-of-most-people-yet-blinded-by-compassion-toward-fell",
    "texto": "Some survivors can be wary of most people, yet blinded by compassion toward fellow survivors or others who suffer — or who pretend to suffer, or exaggerate their sufferings, in order to take advantage of the survivor. Some survivors overidentify with other survivors, not realizing that even if someone was traumatized or suffers in a similar way, it doesn’t necessarily mean that person is honest. Being either overly suspicious or overly trusting can create problems with a partner who is able to judge the sincerity of others more realistically.",
